  "text": "Four grams of SPI was dispersed in 80 mL of distilled water with a magnetic stirrer to prepare SPI solutions. Then, 8 mL of CuSO [CITATION_1] or of ZnCl 2 (20 mmol/L) was dispersed in these SPI solutions. The pH of the mixture was adjusted to about 12 with a NaOH solution and constantly stirred at 25 • C for 10 min. The mixed solution was heated with a magnetic stirrer at 75 • C for 8 h to prepare Cu NCs and Zn NCs.",
